title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: Water Damaged Macbook is turning on but no keyboard or trackpad. I started measuring the pins on the keyboard on pin 30 i have 3.3v that's PP3V3_S3 and pin 4 and 5 i have 3.29v, however on the rest of the pins i get variable voltage goes from 2.9v to 1.7 and up and down up and down. Any ideas ? Also im missing PP18V5_S5 on the trackpad connector

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: Have you tried a known good trackpad and keyboard ?

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: Yes i already tried good known trackpad and keyboard

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: I have 3.3v on pin 49 and pin 22 on U5701, also i have 3.29V on pin 4 and i have 3.29V pin 51(SMC_PME_S4_WAKE_L). What other missing signals would make this chip not functioning ?

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: See if it does do a PRAM reset. Was this liquid damaged?

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: i can't do pram reset but if i press the option then gives me an option to choose the boot device and if i try to connect to wifi i can actually type. So the keyboard working when i have the boot options. ANy ideas

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: And yes the board was water damaged

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: Test all pins of trackpad connector to U5701, could be corroded trace.

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: i checked all for continuity they are all good

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: Check 18V to trackpad, must be plugged in for it to be present.

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: I have 18v when the trackpad is plugged

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: There is not much more to this. Was there corrosion around trackpad/KBD connector?

title: [SOLVED]820-2936-B No trackpad no Keyboard
message: I washed the board again and is working now. Thank you Duke
